            <!-- Introduction Section -->
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-700 mb-4">🚀 Turn Your Python Script into a Clickable App</h2>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    You've built a game-changing Python tool. But here's the problem: <em>your users need Python installed to run it</em>. 
                    With <strong>5.8 million Python developers</strong> worldwide (SlashData, 2023), the demand for shareable apps has never been higher.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    This guide will show you how to convert your <code>.py</code> file to a standalone <code>.exe</code> in <strong>under 5 minutes</strong> using PyInstaller — 
                    no advanced packaging skills required.
                </p>
                
                <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-2">📌 What You'll Learn:</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                        <li>How to <strong>convert Python to EXE</strong> with one command</li>
                        <li>Key PyInstaller flags like <code>--onefile</code> and <code>--windowed</code></li>
                        <li>Where to find your compiled executable (spoiler: it's in the <code>dist/</code> folder)</li>
                        <li>How to add a custom icon to your app</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>

